trans-unit.source: Represents a container for <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Visual3D"></xref> objects.
The <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.ContainerUIElement3D.Children%2A> collection of a ContainerUIElement3D element can only consist of <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> objects.
Adding a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> child to a ContainerUIElement3D implicitly adds it to the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Visual3DCollection> for the ContainerUIElement3D element.
ContainerUIElement3D does not have a visual representation; it serves as a container for other visual 3-D objects.
ContainerUIElement3D is a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> object, which provides support for input, focus, and events in 3-D.
This class does not set the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Visual3D.Visual3DModel%2A> property.
ContainerUIElement3D is introduced in the .NET Framework version 3.5.
For more information, see [Versions and Dependencies](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.ContainerUIElement3D"></xref> class.
ContainerUIElement3D is introduced in the .NET Framework version 3.5.
For more information, see [Versions and Dependencies](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
Gets a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Visual3DCollection"></xref> of child elements of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.ContainerUIElement3D"></xref> object.
The Children collection of a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.ContainerUIElement3D> element can only consist of <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> objects.

Adding a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> child to a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.ContainerUIElement3D> implicitly adds it to the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Visual3DCollection> for the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.ContainerUIElement3D> element.
Children is introduced in the .NET Framework version 3.5.
For more information, see [Versions and Dependencies](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
A <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Visual3DCollection"></xref> of child elements.
The default is an empty collection.
